To display system configuration information on a Windows computer, run msinfo32.exe from the command line. From the Start 
menu, type cmd to start the Command Prompt program and then type msinfo32 into the Command Prompt window. You will get a 
display similar to the one in Figure 1.2, although the information displayed varies, depending on your hardware and the 
version of Windows you are running. As you can see in Figure 1.2, this computer is running Windows 7 Professional. The CPU 
is an Intel™ Core™ 2 Duo CPU T6400 processor running at 2.0 GHz, and the computer has 3 Gbytes of memory, 1.81 Gbytes of 
which is not being used at the time of the display.
